The paper discusses active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on the label complexity of disagreement-based active learning, which falls under the category of computational learning theory. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses applications of the new characterization in computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions agnostic learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
